'''Level 83.1''' is a sublevel between [[Level 83]] and [[Level 84]] in The Backrooms.

==» Overview==
{{Blurimage|file=585New1.png|caption=An image of Level 83.1}}

'''Level 83.1''', commonly known as ''Hills of Hibiscus'', represents an expansive terrain characterized by undulating hills adorned predominantly with vibrant hibiscus-colored grass and various flowers, including lotuses and fluffblooms<ref>Fluffblooms are distinctive flora present in this level, resembling cotton; these flowers are absent in [[The Frontrooms]].</ref>. The level maintains a consistent state during sunset, signifying that the sky will continuously display an orange tint irrespective of the waiting duration. Throughout the level, a faint floral scent permeates the atmosphere, detectable from any location.

The sky displays a spectrum of colors, including blue, pink, crimson, and occasionally white, with intermittent clouds gradually moving across the horizon. Waterways in various shades of pink can be observed throughout the valleys. The temperature remains consistently temperate. The pathways at '''Level 83.1''' do not adhere to a uniform route; rather, they diverge into waterways or ascend toward the skies, separating from the hills.

Certain regions within '''Level 83.1''' demonstrate elevations that surpass their surroundings by as much as 1200 meters, consequently hindering the visibility of the wanderer. The shadows are represented with a minimal level of graphical fidelity, reminiscent of those typically found in video games, despite lacking association with any specific game. Situated behind several hills, there exists what appears to be a valley, currently designated as a sub-section referred to as ''The Hibiscus Valley''.
{{Blurimage|file=585-3.png|caption=Photograph of the Hibiscus Valley}}

=== » The Hibiscus Valley ===
<br>
The Hibiscus Valley is situated in the plains behind the hills, where a diverse array of hibiscus flowers, predominantly in shades of red and pink, can be found. Due to the abundance of flowers, the floral aroma is considerably more pronounced and noticeable compared to most areas within '''Level 83.1'''.

The terrain of the valley is characterized by its soft and gentle nature, facilitating ease of traversal for wanderers. The ground is adorned with a thick layer of grass that appears almost unnaturally lush, complemented by occasional patches of moss, which contribute texture to the landscape. The hibiscus plants grow densely, releasing a floral fragrance that permeates the entire area.

The flowers in The Hibiscus Valley are not pink like everything else in the level, being the only area for such a phenomenon.
{{Blurimage|file=585New2.png|caption=A Pathway that leads to [[Level 118]].}}

=== » The Canopy Pathway ===
<br>
The Canopy Pathway, also known as "The Blossom Maze," is the second-to-last section of '''Level 83.1'''. This region is characterized as a labyrinth layered side by side with cherry blossom trees, making it mildly difficult to navigate, though one can "cheat" by passing through the small gap in the trees. When one walks through the paths, they will experience a strange calming sensation, almost at peace, but still enough to keep them alert.

The leaves that fall from the trees glow faintly, and the closer they get to the ground, the brighter they glow. When they fall onto the trail, they will sink, completely vanishing from sight<ref>The same thing won't happen if they fall on the pink grass.</ref>. The grass beneath the trees is unusually soft, covered in layers of petals that fell over time.

=== » The Lotus Ocean ===
{{Blurimage|file=The_number_of_lotus_is_very_high_that_a_small_part_of_the_ocean_is_revealed_out..png|caption=An image of '''The Lotus Ocean'''. Due to the sheer number of lotuses in this picture, one can only see a part of the ocean.}}
'''The Lotus Ocean''' is a crystal clear, large, faint pinkish water body with hundreds of lotuses growing every minute. The lotus flowers are harmless and are actually edible. However, the flowers cannot be removed from the river without shading it, as they immediately turn into dust under the sun if taken away.

The river's water, known as "Roselight Water," is a pink, drinkable liquid with a faintly sweet flavor reminiscent of strawberry milkshakes. Wanderers who drink from it frequently report feeling refreshed and rejuvenated after enduring insanity. The water is thought to have mild healing properties, helping to relieve fatigue and minor injuries. There are reports of slightly cold currents in the ocean, around 17 degrees Celsius.
Level 83.1 is devoid of hostile entities. However, wanderers have occasionally reported encountering '''Blossom Spirits,''' humanoid [[silhouettes]] that appear to be made of red, glowing petals. These entities are non-hostile and seem to observe wanderers curiously from a distance.
==» Entities==
{{Blurimage|file=585-5.png|caption=An image of Blossom Spirits.}}
'''Level 83.1''' is free of hostile entities. Wanderers have occasionally reported encountering '''Blossom Spirits''', which appear to be humanoid silhouettes made of glowing red petals. These entities appear to be non-hostile and observe wanderers from a distance with curiosity. In addition, '''Blossom Spirits''' are also seen in pink, yellow, and white.

Some wanderers believe the Blossom Spirits are a natural extension of the valley. The distinct energy emitted by the glowing hibiscus flowers and '''Roselight Water''' may have coalesced into sentient forms over time, transforming the spirits into guardians or embodiments of the valley's life force. Their peaceful nature and connection to the flora lend credence to this theory.

Some researchers suggest that Blossom Spirits are not spiritual in nature but instead a form of advanced plant-based life. The glowing hibiscus flowers and other bioluminescent plants in the valley may have evolved into mobile, sentient forms capable of interacting with their environment. Their appearance as glowing, humanoid figures could simply be a mimicry of life forms that wander into the valley.
==» Colonies & Outposts==
There are no colonies and outposts in this level, even though it is suitable for one.
==» Entrances and Exits==
===» Entrances===
*
* Wandering into a specific area in [[Level 83]] could lead one to '''The Hibiscus Valley''' in '''Level 83.1'''.
* Noclipping through a vibrant flower patch in [[Level 10]] may lead to '''Level 83.1'''.
* Falling asleep near a pink sunset-like glow in [[Level 11]] has been known to transport wanderers here.
* It is possible to get here from [[Level 504]], though the method of egress from there is unknown.
* Having a karma rating between 150 and 199 in [[Level 995]] could lead one to this level.
===» Exits===
* Swimming underwater and allowing the current to carry you may transport you to [[Level 37]].
* Climbing the '''Blooming Canopy''' tree and resting under its glowing petals may lead to [[Level 100]].
* Smelling purple flowers in '''The Hibiscus Valley''' can make you fall asleep and wake up in [[Level 626.2]].
* Wandering into a certain section resembling a specific level could lead one into the exact level. An example of this is one getting randomly sent to [[Level 118]] while passing through the '''Canopy Pathway''' area.
